### =====================================================
### Queue Operations (Azure Storage Queue with Managed Identity)
### =====================================================

### Send single message to queue
POST http://localhost:7071/api/queuemessage
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "message": "Hello from logging demo!",
    "count": 1,
    "includeMetadata": true
}

### Send multiple messages for sampling test (5 messages)
POST http://localhost:7071/api/queuemessage
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "message": "Sampling test message",
    "count": 5,
    "includeMetadata": true
}

### Send 50 messages - good for observing sampling behavior
POST http://localhost:7071/api/queuemessage
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "message": "Bulk test message for sampling observation",
    "count": 50,
    "includeMetadata": true
}

### Send 100 messages - maximum for single request
POST http://localhost:7071/api/queuemessage
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "message": "Load test message",
    "count": 100,
    "includeMetadata": false
}

### Check queue status
GET http://localhost:7071/api/queuestatus

### Clear all messages from queue
DELETE http://localhost:7071/api/queueclear

